# Angular conventions

## Components

- Standalone components; `inject()` for DI (match existing files).
- View components list + filter; edit components use reactive forms.
- Destructive actions → dedicated `confirm-*.dialog` component.

## Services

- `@Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })`.
- Export TypeScript interfaces matching backend JSON (`User`, `Domain`, `Profile`).
- API URL constants at top of service (`/passport/api`, `/visita/api/domains`).

## Routing

- Register in `app.routes.ts` with `canActivate: [authGuard]`.
- Use resolvers for list/detail prefetch — avoid duplicate HTTP in `ngOnInit` when resolver exists.

## Roles

- Template: `*role="'passport.admin'"` — exact JWT group name.
- Menu entries in `app.html` must match [docs/domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md).

## Styling

- Shared Less: `styles.less`, `forms.less`, `dialogs.less`.
- Component styles in co-located `.less` or inline `styleUrl` if already used.
- **UI patterns:** [docs/ui/README.md](../../docs/ui/README.md) — mandatory for template work ([backoffice-ui-patterns.mdc](backoffice-ui-patterns.mdc)).

## Domain naming

[domain-model.mdc](domain-model.mdc) — interfaces and labels align with Passport/Visita domain terms.
